  "description": "A **closure** is a [first-class function](./first-class-function.md) bundled together with a reference to the environment in which it was defined. When the function is later called — possibly far from where it was created — it can still access the [variables](/technology/disciplines/computing/software/programming/terms/variable.md) that were in scope at the time of its creation.",
